                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The animated trebuchet has a creature @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Grabbed] in its arm.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The animated trebuchet attempts an Athletics check against the grabbed creature's Fortitude DC.</p>\n<p>On a success, it fires the creature up to 40 feet in height and up to 120 feet away. The creature takes [[/r 4d12[bludgeoning]]] damage plus the appropriate falling damage. If the flung creature lands on another creature, the creature it lands on takes the same amount of bludgeoning damage (@Check[type:reflex|dc:33|basic:true] save).</p>\n<p>On a successful Launch, the animated trebuchet must Interact to reposition its arm into the proper position before it can Launch again.</p>"
                },
